{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/course/dm/note/4/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"mem 的小站"}},"post":{"id":"b5574a02-dfbc-50e6-8cc5-673e4b992e0c","excerpt":"演绎(deduce) 1. 数学归纳法 Mathematical Induction 1.1. 导论 Introduction 数学归纳法(mathematical induction) is used to prove propositions of form  where the domain of…","html":"<p><details open disabled class=\"callout callout-type-quote\"><summary>Word Table</summary><div><p></p><ul>\n<li><strong>演绎(deduce)</strong></li>\n</ul></div></details></p>\n<h2 id=\"1-数学归纳法-Mathematical-Induction\" style=\"position:relative;\">1. 数学归纳法 Mathematical Induction<a href=\"#1-%E6%95%B0%E5%AD%A6%E5%BD%92%E7%BA%B3%E6%B3%95-Mathematical-Induction\" aria-label=\"1 数学归纳法 Mathematical Induction permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"11-导论-Introduction\" style=\"position:relative;\">1.1. 导论 Introduction<a href=\"#11-%E5%AF%BC%E8%AE%BA-Introduction\" aria-label=\"11 导论 Introduction permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p><strong>数学归纳法(mathematical induction)</strong> is used to prove propositions of form <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>n</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\forall n\\ P(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> where the domain of discourse is the set of positive integers:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>∧</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>k</mi><mo>≥</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>n</mi><mo>≥</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P(n_0) \\land \\forall k\\ge n_0 (P(k)\\rightarrow P(k+1)) \\rightarrow \\forall n\\ge n_0 (P(n))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∧</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8304em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8304em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p><details open disabled class=\"callout callout-type-note\"><summary>More general form of the proof procedure</summary><div><p></p><p>(1) <strong>Basis step</strong>: Establish <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P(1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p><p>(2) <strong>Inductive step</strong>: Prove that <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P(k)\\rightarrow P(k+1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> for <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k\\ge 1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8304em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span>.</p><p><strong>Conclusion</strong>: The basis step and the inductive step together imply <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>n</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\forall n\\ P(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p></div></details></p>\n<h3 id=\"12-数学归纳法的证明-Proof-of-Mathematical-Induction\" style=\"position:relative;\">1.2. 数学归纳法的证明 Proof of Mathematical Induction<a href=\"#12-%E6%95%B0%E5%AD%A6%E5%BD%92%E7%BA%B3%E6%B3%95%E7%9A%84%E8%AF%81%E6%98%8E-Proof-of-Mathematical-Induction\" aria-label=\"12 数学归纳法的证明 Proof of Mathematical Induction permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p><strong>良序性(well-ordering property)</strong>：Every nonempty set of nonnegative integers has a least element.</p>\n<p>The <strong>有效性(validity)</strong> of mathematical induction follows from the well-ordering property for the set of positive integers (<span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi><mo>+</mo></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{Z}_+</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8972em;vertical-align:-0.2083em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2583em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2083em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>).</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://static.memset0.cn/img/v6/2024/03/26/xRMQ9YRg.png\"alt=\"\" style=\"width: 550px; \" ></p>\n<h2 id=\"2-完全归纳法-Strong-Induction\" style=\"position:relative;\">2. 完全归纳法 Strong Induction<a href=\"#2-%E5%AE%8C%E5%85%A8%E5%BD%92%E7%BA%B3%E6%B3%95-Strong-Induction\" aria-label=\"2 完全归纳法 Strong Induction permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"21-导论-Introduction\" style=\"position:relative;\">2.1. 导论 Introduction<a href=\"#21-%E5%AF%BC%E8%AE%BA-Introduction\" aria-label=\"21 导论 Introduction permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p><strong>完全归纳法(strong induction)</strong> or <strong>第二数学归纳法(second principle of mathematical induction)</strong>：</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>∧</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>k</mi><mo>≥</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>∧</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>∧</mo><mo>⋯</mo><mo>∧</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>n</mi><mo>≥</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P(n_0) \\land \\forall k\\ge n_0 (P(n_0) \\land P(n_0+1) \\land \\cdots \\land P(k) \\rightarrow P(k+1)) \\rightarrow \\forall n\\ge n_0 (P(n))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∧</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8304em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∧</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∧</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.5556em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\">⋯</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∧</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8304em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p><details open disabled class=\"callout callout-type-note\"><summary>More general form of the proof procedure</summary><div><p></p><p>(1) <strong>Basis step</strong>: Establish <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P(n_0)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p><p>(2) <strong>Inductive step</strong>: Prove <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>∧</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>∧</mo><mo>⋯</mo><mo>∧</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P(n_0) \\land P(n_0 + 1) \\land \\cdots \\land P(k) \\rightarrow P(k+1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∧</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∧</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.5556em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\">⋯</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∧</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p><p><strong>Conclusion</strong>: The basis step sand the inductive step allow one to conclude that <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>n</mi><mo>≥</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\forall n\\ge n_0 P(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8304em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p></div></details></p>\n<p>Note:\nThe validities of both mathematical induction and strong induction follow from the well-ordering property.\nIn fact, mathematical induction, strong induction, and well-ordering are all equivalent principles.</p>\n<h3 id=\"22-计算几何中的完全归纳法-Using-Strong-Induction-in-Computational-Geometry\" style=\"position:relative;\">2.2. 计算几何中的完全归纳法 Using Strong Induction in Computational Geometry<a href=\"#22-%E8%AE%A1%E7%AE%97%E5%87%A0%E4%BD%95%E4%B8%AD%E7%9A%84%E5%AE%8C%E5%85%A8%E5%BD%92%E7%BA%B3%E6%B3%95-Using-Strong-Induction-in-Computational-Geometry\" aria-label=\"22 计算几何中的完全归纳法 Using Strong Induction in Computational Geometry permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Some terms:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>多边形(polygon)</strong>、<strong>边(side)</strong>、<strong>顶点(vertex)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>简单多边形(simple polygon)</strong>：简单多边形没有边相交。Every simple polygon divides the plane into two regions: its <strong>内部(interior)</strong>, its <strong>外部(exterior)</strong>.</li>\n<li><strong>对角线(diagonal)</strong>：连接任意两个非相邻节点的线段。</li>\n<li><strong>内对角线(interior diagonal)</strong>：完全在简单多边形内部的对角线。</li>\n<li><strong>凸多边形(convex)</strong>：凸多边形中的所有对角线均不边相交。或者说，凸多边形一定是简单多边形且所有对角线都是内对角线。</li>\n<li><strong>三角剖分(triangulation)</strong>：将多边形划分成若干个不重叠的三角形。</li>\n</ul>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#1-%E6%95%B0%E5%AD%A6%E5%BD%92%E7%BA%B3%E6%B3%95-mathematical-induction\">1. 数学归纳法 Mathematical Induction</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#11-%E5%AF%BC%E8%AE%BA-introduction\">1.1. 导论 Introduction</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#12-%E6%95%B0%E5%AD%A6%E5%BD%92%E7%BA%B3%E6%B3%95%E7%9A%84%E8%AF%81%E6%98%8E-proof-of-mathematical-induction\">1.2. 数学归纳法的证明 Proof of Mathematical Induction</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#2-%E5%AE%8C%E5%85%A8%E5%BD%92%E7%BA%B3%E6%B3%95-strong-induction\">2. 完全归纳法 Strong Induction</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#21-%E5%AF%BC%E8%AE%BA-introduction\">2.1. 导论 Introduction</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#22-%E8%AE%A1%E7%AE%97%E5%87%A0%E4%BD%95%E4%B8%AD%E7%9A%84%E5%AE%8C%E5%85%A8%E5%BD%92%E7%BA%B3%E6%B3%95-using-strong-induction-in-computational-geometry\">2.2. 计算几何中的完全归纳法 Using Strong Induction in Computational Geometry</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Ch5 Induction and Recursion","date":null,"description":null},"fields":{"cover":null,"slug":"/course/dm/note/4/","isDoc":true,"category":"[{\"name\":\"课程笔记\",\"to\":\"/course/\"}]","propsJson":null}},"previous":null,"next":null},"pageContext":{"id":"b5574a02-dfbc-50e6-8cc5-673e4b992e0c","previousPostId":null,"nextPostId":null,"navJson":"[{\"slug\":\"/course/dm\",\"file\":\"/home/runner/work/gatsby-blog/gatsby-blog/content/course/dm/index.md\",\"title\":\"Intro\"},{\"title\":\"Notes\",\"children\":[{\"slug\":\"/course/dm/note/1\",\"file\":\"/home/runner/work/gatsby-blog/gatsby-blog/content/course/dm/note/1.md\",\"title\":\"Ch1 Logic & Proofs\"},{\"slug\":\"/course/dm/note/2\",\"file\":\"/home/runner/work/gatsby-blog/gatsby-blog/content/course/dm/note/2.md\",\"title\":\"Ch2 Basic Structures\"},{\"slug\":\"/course/dm/note/3\",\"file\":\"/home/runner/work/gatsby-blog/gat